.TH GIT-PR-LAND 1 "2026-06-13" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-pr-land \- land one ready GitHub pull request
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git pr-land
.RI [ options ]
.I number|url|branch
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git pr-land
verifies that one GitHub pull request is ready, merges it, syncs the base
branch locally, and deletes the local pull request branch.
.PP
This command intentionally does not discover or land stacks. Use
.BR git-pr-land-stack (1)
for stack orchestration.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-method " " \fImethod\fR
Merge method:
.BR squash ,
.BR merge ,
or
.BR rebase .
Defaults to
.BR squash .
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-branch
Do not ask GitHub to delete the remote branch and do not delete the local
branch.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Print actions without changing anything.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Pull request was landed.
.TP
.B 1
Pull request is not ready or merge failed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or local environment error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-pr-ready (1),
.BR git-pr-stack (1),
.BR git-pr-land-stack (1)
